OL,4,CObservatory to boost south of Scotland
OL,5,Ctourism
OL,7,FOnce completed the space will offer
OL,8,Feducational spaces, an exhibition
OL,9,Farea, a gift shop and a cafe. With the
OL,10,Fplanned telescope equipment, visitors
OL,11,Fwill be able to see numerous nebulae,
OL,12,Fstar clusters and galaxies, which are
OL,13,Fdifficult or impossible to view from
OL,14,Furban or light polluted skies.
OL,16,FThe observatory will also be well
OL,17,Fplaced to observe transient phenomena
OL,18,Flike meteor showers, aurora, and
OL,19,Fcomets, as well as providing daytime
OL,20,Fviewing of the sun through specialised
OL,21,Fsolar telescopes.
